Array: [9, 2, 7, 4, 5, 8, 1, 6, 3]
Median: 5
```

The `partition` function is a standard part of the Quickselect algorithm and is used to partition the array around a pivot element. The `quickselect` function recursively finds the kth smallest element in the array using the partition function. The `median` function determines whether the length of the array is odd or even and calls the `quickselect` function accordingly.

