In the recursive case, we call the function again with `n - 1` as the new value for `n` and `acc * n` as the new value for `acc`. By multiplying `acc` with `n`, we keep track of the running product.

Since this function is tail-recursive, the final recursive call is the last operation performed in each recursive step, making it possible to optimize the function to have O(1) time complexity.

