2. Base case: If `num` is less than or equal to 0, return 0.

3. Recursive case:
   a. Initialize a variable `digit` to be the last digit of `num` (i.e., `num % 10`).
   b. If `digit` is divisible by 3, call `sumOfDigits` with `num // 10` (i.e., `num` without the last digit).
   c. Otherwise, return `digit + sumOfDigits(num // 10)`.

