We'll start by initializing dp[0][0] with the value of the first cell in the input array. Then, we'll iterate over each cell in the first row and first column, and update dp accordingly.

For each cell (i, j), we'll check if the cell contains a prime number. If it does, we'll set dp[i][j] to -1, indicating that this cell cannot be part of the path. If the cell does not contain a prime number, we'll update dp[i][j] as follows:

- If the cell is the first cell in the first row (j=0), we'll set dp[i][j] to the sum of the previous cell in the same row and the value of the current cell.
- If the cell is the first cell in the first column (i=0), we'll set dp[i][j] to the sum of the previous cell in the same column and the value of the current cell.
- Otherwise, we'll set dp[i][j] to the maximum of the previous cell in the same row and the previous cell in the same column, plus the value of the current cell.

After iterating over all cells, the maximum path sum will be stored in dp[m-1][n-1], where m and n are the dimensions of the input array.

